    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 536.]</seg>w <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 31, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 12th of March (No. 346) has
                    been received.</p>
                <p>Your attendance at the nuptial ceremonies of his royal highness the Prince of
                    Wales, and the honors which you paid to the ceremony at the legation, are
                    approved. The event is regarded by the British nation as contributing a new
                    guaranty of the stability, prosperity, and welfare of the United Kingdom. The
                    people of the United States, well-wishers to all nations, and cordially friendly
                    to Great Britain, give their best wishes that that guaranty may prove a
                    substantial and reliable one.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
